Viva Questions
What is Validation Rule?

A validation rule prevents invalid data from being saved in Salesforce.

Why use Validation Rules?

To maintain data accuracy and consistency.

Difference between Object and Field?
Object stores records.
Field stores attributes/data inside records.
What is Lightning App?

A collection of tabs and features in Salesforce Lightning Experience.

What is Unique Field?

A field that does not allow duplicate values.

i was going to create a custom tab object and then  a new lightning app from that custom tab object but the custom tab object dropdown only allows 1 object so how do i combine student and faculty or how do i make the lightning app

You should create 2 separate Custom Object Tabs first:

Student Tab
Faculty Tab

Because Salesforce allows one tab = one object.

So you do NOT combine Student and Faculty into one tab.

Correct Flow
Step 1 → Create Student Object

Create:

Student__c

Then create its tab:

Student Tab
Step 2 → Create Faculty Object

Create:

Faculty__c

Then create its tab:

Faculty Tab
Step 3 → Create Lightning App

Now go to:

Setup → App Manager → New Lightning App
While Creating Lightning App

After entering:

App Name = College Management System

Click:

Next → Next

Then you will reach:

Navigation Items

There you can add MULTIPLE tabs.

Move these from left to right:

Student
Faculty

using:

Add >

Now both objects appear inside ONE Lightning App.

Final Result

Inside your Lightning App:

College Management System
    ├── Student Tab
    └── Faculty Tab

So:

Separate Objects
Separate Tabs
One Combined Lightning App
Important

The dropdown you saw during:

New Custom Object Tab

is only for selecting ONE object for ONE tab.
